WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.422 --> 00:00:11.391
Good evening.
I've been asked to tell you...

2
00:00:11.492 --> 00:00:14.086
that the following show
is very scary...

3
00:00:14.195 --> 00:00:16.789
with stuff that might
give your kids nightmares.

4
00:00:16.898 --> 00:00:20.197
You see. there are
some crybabies out there-

5
00:00:20.301 --> 00:00:23.293
religious types mostly-
who might be offended.

6
00:00:23.404 --> 00:00:27.773
If you are one of them.
I advise you to turn off your set now.

7
00:00:27.875 --> 00:00:29.775
Come on. I dare ya.

8
00:00:29.877 --> 00:00:33.369
Chicken.

9
00:01:09.978 --> 00:01:12.071
Behold mighty Caesar...

10
00:01:12.180 --> 00:01:14.273
in all his glory!

11
00:01:17.052 --> 00:01:18.986
D'oh!

12
00:01:20.222 --> 00:01:23.658
I am Calliope.
the muse of heroic poetry.

13
00:01:23.759 --> 00:01:26.023
No kiddin'.

14
00:01:28.730 --> 00:01:31.631
Stupid party.
Wish we was trick-or-treating.

15
00:01:31.733 --> 00:01:35.430
Now. Bart. you can find
just as much horror around the house.

16
00:01:35.537 --> 00:01:37.437
Now. you children
may not know it...

17
00:01:37.539 --> 00:01:39.769
but there was once
an evil witch...

18
00:01:39.875 --> 00:01:43.106
and she died a horrible death.

19
00:01:45.414 --> 00:01:49.407
- These are her eyes.
- Eww!

20
00:01:49.518 --> 00:01:51.543
And this is her hair.

21
00:01:52.788 --> 00:01:56.622
- Eww!
- And these are her brains.

22
00:01:56.725 --> 00:01:58.750
Eww!

23
00:01:58.860 --> 00:02:01.351
Yo. Mom.
We haven't got the eyeballs yet.

24
00:02:01.297 --> 00:02:03.197
Homer. you're ruining it.

25
00:02:03.299 --> 00:02:05.767
Yeah. well. it was an evil game.

26
00:02:05.868 --> 00:02:08.996
Well. now we need
another Halloween activity.

27
00:02:09.105 --> 00:02:11.733
Hmm. Does anyone know
a ghost story?

28
00:02:11.841 --> 00:02:14.571
I do. It's a story
Of a boy and his doll.

29
00:02:14.677 --> 00:02:17.543
- That's not so scary.
- A doll... from hell!

30
00:02:17.578 --> 00:02:20.409
I'm gonna go to the store.

31
00:02:24.119 --> 00:02:26.815
Happy birthday. Bart.

32
00:02:26.922 --> 00:02:29.015
Thanks. Grampa.

33
00:02:29.124 --> 00:02:31.024
- Where'd you get all the money?
- The government.

34
00:02:31.126 --> 00:02:33.458
I didn't earn it.
I don't need it.

35
00:02:33.562 --> 00:02:37.293
But if they miss one payment.
I'll raise hell!

36
00:02:37.399 --> 00:02:39.299
Hey. Homer.
where's your present?

37
00:02:39.401 --> 00:02:42.632
D'oh! I mean. don't worry. son.

38
00:02:42.738 --> 00:02:45.104
I forgot to get you a present.

39
00:02:45.207 --> 00:02:47.573
But I swear
on my father's grave-

40
00:02:47.676 --> 00:02:50.702
- Hey!
- I will get you one now.

41
00:02:57.586 --> 00:02:59.486
Do you sell toys?

42
00:02:59.588 --> 00:03:03.581
We sell forbidden objects
from places men fear to tread.

43
00:03:03.692 --> 00:03:07.128
We also sell frozen yogurt.
which I call frogurt.

44
00:03:07.229 --> 00:03:09.424
Well. I need something
for my son's birthday.

45
00:03:09.531 --> 00:03:11.931
Uh. perhaps this
will please the gentleman.

46
00:03:17.873 --> 00:03:20.481
Take this object.
But beware- it carries a terrible curse.

47
00:03:20.516 --> 00:03:23.090
- Ooh. that's bad.
- But it comes with a free frogurt.

48
00:03:23.190 --> 00:03:26.353
- That's good.
- The frogurt is also cursed.

49
00:03:26.460 --> 00:03:29.395
- That's bad.
- But you get your choice of topping.

50
00:03:29.497 --> 00:03:32.830
- That's good!
- The toppings contain potassium benzoate.

51
00:03:34.936 --> 00:03:37.029
- That's bad.
- Can I go now?

52
00:03:39.874 --> 00:03:41.774
Happy birthday. son.

53
00:03:43.611 --> 00:03:47.069
Great Caesar's Ghost!
A talking Krusty doll!

54
00:03:48.749 --> 00:03:52.549
I'm Krusty the Clown.
and I love you very much.

55
00:03:52.653 --> 00:03:56.555
Oh. Dad. this is
the best birthday I've ever had.

56
00:03:56.657 --> 00:04:00.525
That doll is evil.
I tells ya. Evil!

57
00:04:00.628 --> 00:04:03.290
E- E-Evil!

58
00:04:03.397 --> 00:04:05.695
Grampa. you said that
about all the presents.

59
00:04:05.800 --> 00:04:06.185
I just want attention.

60
00:04:06.220 --> 00:04:08.518
And in environmental news...

61
00:04:08.623 --> 00:04:10.750
scientists have announced
that Springfield's air...

62
00:04:10.858 --> 00:04:13.622
is now only dangerous
to children and the elderly.

63
00:04:13.728 --> 00:04:15.662
Whoo-hoo!

64
00:04:17.098 --> 00:04:19.589
I'm Krusty the Clown.
and I don't like you.

65
00:04:21.703 --> 00:04:24.968
I'm Krusty the Clown.
and I'm going to kill you.

66
00:04:25.073 --> 00:04:28.065
Didn't even pull the string that time.

67
00:04:28.176 --> 00:04:31.577
I said I'm going to kill you.
You. Homer Simpson.

68
00:04:31.679 --> 00:04:34.113
Oh. yeah? With what?

69
00:04:34.215 --> 00:04:36.547
Aah!

70
00:04:37.585 --> 00:04:39.815
Homer. what's wrong?

71
00:04:39.921 --> 00:04:42.947
That doll tried to kill me.

72
00:04:43.057 --> 00:04:47.289
I'd say that the pressure's finally
gotten to Dad. but what pressure?

73
00:04:47.395 --> 00:04:49.260
Don't leave me alone with him.

74
00:05:11.819 --> 00:05:13.623
Scram!

75
00:05:13.658 --> 00:05:17.492
There goes the last lingering thread
Of my heterosexuality.

76
00:05:19.564 --> 00:05:22.761
Hey. baby. get comfortable.
Relax.

77
00:05:22.868 --> 00:05:25.564
It's a little hot for that cheerleader outfit.
don't you think?

78
00:05:29.574 --> 00:05:34.568
You think your dirty socks can stop me?

79
00:05:34.679 --> 00:05:37.842
Well. they are making me dizzy.

80
00:05:50.462 --> 00:05:52.896
Good-bye. dolly.

81
00:05:53.932 --> 00:05:55.832
Arrivederci. Vito.

82
00:05:55.934 --> 00:06:00.064
I was a fool to think anyone would want
Nude photos of Whoopi Goldberg.

83
00:06:00.172 --> 00:06:02.072
What the-

84
00:06:03.909 --> 00:06:06.776
And that is that.

85
00:06:09.948 --> 00:06:13.247
Guess who. fat boy!

86
00:06:13.351 --> 00:06:16.809
- Marge! Marge. look!
- Oh. my God!

87
00:06:16.922 --> 00:06:19.152
The doll's trying to kill me.
and the toaster's been laughing at me.

88
00:06:19.257 --> 00:06:22.226
Eww! Dog water.

89
00:06:25.330 --> 00:06:29.528
Your doll is trying to kill my husband!

90
00:06:29.634 --> 00:06:31.534
Yes. I'll hold.

91
00:06:43.181 --> 00:06:45.479
Yep. here's your problem.

92
00:06:45.584 --> 00:06:48.212
Someone set this thing
to "evil. "

93
00:06:49.321 --> 00:06:52.256
- I love you. Homer.
- Come here. you!

94
00:06:56.061 --> 00:06:58.461
- Here you go. buddy.
- Did you walk the dog?

95
00:06:58.563 --> 00:06:59.548
Yeah. he buried me
a couple of times.

96
00:06:59.583 --> 00:07:00.534
Yeah. dogs like to
bury old junk.

97
00:07:00.642 --> 00:07:02.906
Yeah. you stupid idiot.

98
00:07:04.346 --> 00:07:06.541
Oh. what a day.

99
00:07:06.648 --> 00:07:10.414
Homer made me give him a sponge bath.

100
00:07:10.518 --> 00:07:12.918
But coming home to you
makes it all worthwhile.

101
00:07:15.023 --> 00:07:17.082
Here. let me get that for you.

102
00:07:21.563 --> 00:07:26.626
So then his wife
comes through the door!

103
00:07:26.735 --> 00:07:28.669
- So?
- Did I mention she was dead?

104
00:07:27.456 --> 00:07:27.526
- No.
- Well. she was.

105
00:07:27.561 --> 00:07:31.463
And she hit him in the head
with a golf club.

106
00:07:31.565 --> 00:07:33.465
- And?
- Don't you remember?

107
00:07:33.567 --> 00:07:35.865
He went golfing all the time.
and it really bugged her.

108
00:07:35.969 --> 00:07:38.460
- You said he went bowling.
- D'oh!

109
00:07:38.572 --> 00:07:42.372
Homer. I've coughed up
scarier stuff than that.

110
00:07:42.476 --> 00:07:46.173
Grampa. why don't you tell us a story?
You've led an interesting life.

111
00:07:46.280 --> 00:07:48.180
That's a lie. and you know it!

112
00:07:48.282 --> 00:07:51.683
But I have seen a lot of movies.

113
00:07:59.359 --> 00:08:00.125
My name is Marge Bouvier.
I'm here about your ad.

114
00:08:00.160 --> 00:08:04.096
"Single white female wanted
for mysterious expedition.

115
00:08:04.197 --> 00:08:07.598
Must like monkeys.
Nonsmoker preferred. "

116
00:08:07.701 --> 00:08:09.601
Well. you'd be
a welcome change of pace...

117
00:08:09.703 --> 00:08:11.796
from the rest of these
crude and uncouth sailors.

118
00:08:11.905 --> 00:08:15.898
- Arr!Arr!Arr!
- Arr!Arr!Arr!

119
00:08:16.009 --> 00:08:19.240
- What do you think. Smithers?
- I think women and seamen don't mix.

120
00:08:19.346 --> 00:08:23.942
We know what you think.
Young lady. you're hired.

121
00:08:29.789 --> 00:08:32.189
Hey. I heard we're going
to Ape Island.

122
00:08:32.292 --> 00:08:34.192
Yeah. to capture a giant ape.

123
00:08:34.294 --> 00:08:36.194
I wish we were going
to Candy Apple Island.

124
00:08:36.296 --> 00:08:38.662
Candy Apple Island?
What do they got there?

125
00:08:38.765 --> 00:08:41.165
Apes. but they're not so big.

126
00:08:41.267 --> 00:08:43.292
Homer! Homer! Homer!

127
00:08:43.403 --> 00:08:45.803
Hey. who's this Homer dude?

128
00:08:45.905 --> 00:08:49.068
He's either a 50-foot
prehistoric ape...

129
00:08:49.175 --> 00:08:52.269
or a tourist trap concocted
by the Ape Island Jaycees.

130
00:08:52.379 --> 00:08:56.338
- Either way. we're going ashore.
- Am I going too?

131
00:08:56.449 --> 00:08:59.350
Of course. We wouldn't think
Of going without the bait.

132
00:08:59.452 --> 00:09:02.216
Uh. that is.
the bait-thing beauty.

133
00:09:02.322 --> 00:09:04.222
The bathing beauty.

134
00:09:04.324 --> 00:09:06.224
I covered that up pretty well.

135
00:09:06.326 --> 00:09:08.692
Homer!Homer!Homer!

136
00:09:08.795 --> 00:09:12.458
Homer! Homer! Homer! Homer!

137
00:09:12.565 --> 00:09:14.931
Just try to remain inconspicuous.

138
00:09:16.079 --> 00:09:19.139
we wouldn't dream of sacrificing
the blue-haired woman.

139
00:09:19.248 --> 00:09:21.978
Oh. well. isn't that-
Whoa!

140
00:09:22.085 --> 00:09:25.384
Mm-hmm.

141
00:09:32.028 --> 00:09:35.589
Huh? D'oh!

142
00:09:35.698 --> 00:09:38.599
D'oh! D'oh! D'oh!

143
00:09:46.909 --> 00:09:49.275
Smithers. this is
a golden opportunity.

144
00:09:49.378 --> 00:09:52.438
If we get him alive.
we can put him on Broadway.

145
00:09:52.548 --> 00:09:55.517
Dead. we'll sell
monkey stew to the army.

146
00:09:55.618 --> 00:09:57.779
Ooh!

147
00:09:57.887 --> 00:10:00.287
Keep your hands
To yourself. mister.

148
00:10:03.326 --> 00:10:06.784
Now we don't want to kill him.

149
00:10:06.896 --> 00:10:08.830
Shoot him around
The groin and belly.

150
00:10:15.438 --> 00:10:18.135
Hey. Homer. cut it out.
Come on. quit eating me.

151
00:10:18.170 --> 00:10:22.368
All right. you big ape.
Get a snoot full of this gas bomb.

152
00:10:42.064 --> 00:10:44.191
Nice work. Smithers.

153
00:10:44.300 --> 00:10:46.666
When we get back.
I'm giving you a raise.

154
00:10:46.769 --> 00:10:50.637
Oh. well.

155
00:11:01.906 --> 00:11:03.897
What kind of show
you got for us. Mr. Burns?

156
00:11:04.008 --> 00:11:07.500
Well. the ape's going to stand around
for three hours or so.

157
00:11:07.612 --> 00:11:12.106
Then we'll close with the ethnic comedy
Of Dugan and Dershowitz.

158
00:11:12.216 --> 00:11:13.945
Sensational!

159
00:11:14.051 --> 00:11:15.951
Ladies and gentlemen...

160
00:11:16.053 --> 00:11:17.953
in his native land.
he was a king.

161
00:11:18.055 --> 00:11:21.855
But he comes before you in chains
For your own amusement.

162
00:11:21.959 --> 00:11:25.861
Presenting Homer-
the Eighth Wonder of the World!

163
00:11:28.065 --> 00:11:32.024
Wow! Look at the size
Of that platform!

164
00:11:40.444 --> 00:11:42.605
I think you're making him angry.

165
00:11:42.713 --> 00:11:46.911
Come on. What's he gonna do?
Run amok in downtown Springfield?

166
00:11:59.263 --> 00:12:02.699
Hey. monkey. you want a peanut?

167
00:12:02.800 --> 00:12:06.861
I said one!

168
00:12:23.728 --> 00:12:26.219
I'm dreading the reviews.
I can tell you that.

169
00:12:26.331 --> 00:12:28.299
Oh. hi. Homie.

170
00:12:40.845 --> 00:12:42.369
Oh!

171
00:12:45.083 --> 00:12:47.950
- He's sure taking his sweet time.
- Better refuel.

172
00:12:51.856 --> 00:12:53.756
You know. you look
a little flushed.

173
00:12:53.858 --> 00:12:56.088
Maybe you should eat
more vegetables and less people.

174
00:12:56.194 --> 00:13:00.290
Uh-huh.

175
00:13:05.603 --> 00:13:07.503
He's not dead!

176
00:13:07.605 --> 00:13:09.698
No. but his career is.

177
00:13:09.807 --> 00:13:13.903
I remember when Al Jolson ran amok at the
Winter Garden and climbed the Chrysler Building.

178
00:13:14.012 --> 00:13:16.412
After that.
he couldn't get arrested in this town.

179
00:13:18.516 --> 00:13:22.509
Don't worry. Homie.
I'll take care of you.

180
00:13:28.459 --> 00:13:30.359
Are you with the bride or groom?

181
00:13:30.394 --> 00:13:31.148
Right this way.

182
00:13:34.186 --> 00:13:37.280
Folks. if you could just stop cleaning
each other for a second.

183
00:13:37.389 --> 00:13:39.880
Wait. Wait. Marge.
I can't find your father.

184
00:13:44.296 --> 00:13:46.628
Oh. Homer.

185
00:13:47.962 --> 00:13:49.862
Now. kids. instead of candy...

186
00:13:49.964 --> 00:13:52.694
I thought I'd serve
an array of healthy fresh fruits.

187
00:13:54.902 --> 00:13:56.961
Fruit is nature's candy.

188
00:14:00.208 --> 00:14:03.871
Whoa!

189
00:14:06.247 --> 00:14:08.374
Hey. hi. fellow Halloweenies.

190
00:14:08.483 --> 00:14:10.474
Did I scaredely-dareya?

191
00:14:10.585 --> 00:14:14.077
Dag- darn it!

192
00:14:14.188 --> 00:14:17.123
Nice try. Mr. Flanders.
but I've got a story so scary...

193
00:14:17.225 --> 00:14:20.456
- you'll wet your pants.
- Too late.

194
00:14:25.833 --> 00:14:28.233
From "A" apple to "Z" zebra...

195
00:14:28.336 --> 00:14:32.773
Baby's First Pop-up Book
is 26 pages of alphabetic adventure.

196
00:14:32.874 --> 00:14:36.833
Bart. you mean to tell me
you read a book intended for preschoolers?

197
00:14:34.687 --> 00:14:36.868
- Well. most of it.
- You have to read another book.

198
00:14:47.293 --> 00:14:50.888
Gee. never noticed that before.

199
00:15:01.807 --> 00:15:03.866
Ow! What's this?

200
00:15:05.411 --> 00:15:07.311
- Evil!
- Evil!

201
00:15:07.413 --> 00:15:10.644
- Madness. -
Beware! - Beware!

202
00:15:10.750 --> 00:15:14.447
- Cool!
- Ow! Ow! Ow!

203
00:15:18.524 --> 00:15:20.424
"Chapter Eight:
Let's Talk Zombies.

204
00:15:19.991 --> 00:15:24.291
You must walk the earth. feeding on the brains
Of the living until the spell is broken. "

205
00:15:24.395 --> 00:15:28.957
Bart. please. Don't you remember that
Snowball I died four years ago tonight?

206
00:15:29.066 --> 00:15:32.524
Run over by the mayor's
beer-swilling brother. Clovis.

207
00:15:32.637 --> 00:15:35.367
Hey. maybe there's a spell in here
that'll bring her back from the dead.

208
00:15:36.407 --> 00:15:38.307
Let's see what we've got.

209
00:15:38.409 --> 00:15:40.309
"How To Get Your Skeletons
Their Whitest.

210
00:15:40.411 --> 00:15:42.311
Selling Your Soul
In A Buyer's Market. "

211
00:15:42.413 --> 00:15:45.143
Ah. here we are.
"How To Raise The Dead. "

212
00:16:04.435 --> 00:16:09.168
"Cullen. Rayburn. Narz. Trebek. "

213
00:16:11.575 --> 00:16:15.443
"Zabar. Kresge. Caldor. Wal-Mart!"

214
00:16:21.218 --> 00:16:24.278
It's not working.

215
00:16:25.423 --> 00:16:29.325
Bart. you cast the wrong spell.
Zombies!

216
00:16:29.427 --> 00:16:33.261
Please. Lise. they prefer
to be called "the living impaired. "

217
00:16:39.064 --> 00:16:42.124
Well. howdy. strangers.
What can I do ya for?

218
00:16:42.234 --> 00:16:45.032
Brains. Brains.

219
00:16:45.136 --> 00:16:48.970
Why. Sue Dokes. you rascal.
I thought you were dead and-

220
00:16:52.210 --> 00:16:54.371
Dad. we did something very bad!

221
00:16:54.479 --> 00:16:56.106
- Did you wreck the car?
- No.

222
00:16:56.214 --> 00:16:58.273
- Did you raise the dead?
- Yes!

223
00:16:58.383 --> 00:17:00.283
- But the car's okay?
- Uh-huh.

224
00:17:00.385 --> 00:17:03.047
All right. then.

225
00:17:04.289 --> 00:17:06.689
Martin Prince.
report to my office at once.

226
00:17:06.791 --> 00:17:11.558
And bring that big. juicy.
chess club brain of yours along with you.

227
00:17:11.663 --> 00:17:13.688
Mmm.

228
00:17:15.767 --> 00:17:19.760
Hey. kids. look what you can win
in the Krusty Sweepstakes.

229
00:17:25.844 --> 00:17:28.608
To enter. send me
your parents' brains...

230
00:17:28.713 --> 00:17:32.171
or write "Parents' Brains"
on a three-by-five card and send it to-

231
00:17:32.284 --> 00:17:34.684
Homer. did you
barricade the door?

232
00:17:34.786 --> 00:17:37.687
Why? Oh. the zombies. No.

233
00:17:40.425 --> 00:17:43.326
Spare my family.
Take me. Take me.

234
00:17:43.428 --> 00:17:47.330
Hmm?

235
00:17:47.432 --> 00:17:50.731
- Brains! Brains!
- Brains! Brains!

236
00:17:52.404 --> 00:17:55.100
I thought dabbling in the black arts
would be good for a chuckle.

237
00:17:55.206 --> 00:17:58.403
How wrong I was.
I should have never read that book.

238
00:17:58.510 --> 00:18:01.479
Wait. Bart. Maybe the library has
another book that will reverse the spell.

239
00:18:01.579 --> 00:18:03.479
It's our only hope.

240
00:18:03.581 --> 00:18:05.913
To the book depository.

241
00:18:10.302 --> 00:18:12.827
Hey. Simpson.
I'm feeling a mite peckish.

242
